name: Leagues Cup
summary: Several MLS teams have competed in the Leagues Cup 2024, with varying results. FC Cincinnati defeated Santos Laguna in penalty kicks, while the Sounders FC advanced to the quarterfinals with a 4-0 win over Pumas UNAM. However, the Portland Timbers were eliminated by St. Louis CITY SC, who later lost to Club América. The Colorado Rapids and New England Revolution also advanced, while Inter Miami CF will face the Columbus Crew in the Round of 16. Some MLS fans are boycotting the tournament due to concerns about player health and the perceived lack of competitive balance. The round of 16 matchups and schedule for the Leagues Cup are available on MLSsoccer.com.

name: McDonald's Collector cups
summary: McDonald's has launched a highly anticipated promotion featuring limited-edition collector's cups. Starting August 13th, these exclusive cups are available with the purchase of the newly released Happy Meals for adults and Collector's Meals. The cups showcase iconic pop-culture moments and come in a set of six. While the promotion is available now in Canada, customers in the United States can only obtain the cups by visiting participating McDonald's locations. The promotion has generated significant excitement and is expected to be met with enthusiasm from collectors and fans alike.

summary: The Pixel 9 Pro and 9 Pro XL have been released, but reviewers are suggesting that a different Pixel phone may be a better buy. AT&T is offering deals on the Pixel 9 series. Forbes predicts that the Pixel 9 Pro will revolutionize smartphones. ZDNet compares the Pixel 9 Pro XL to the iPhone, highlighting its positive aspects. name: Tina Peters
summary: Tina Peters, a former Mesa County clerk, has been found guilty on seven counts related to a voting machine data leak. The trial has garnered national attention due to Peters' ties to Dominion Voting conspiracies. During the proceedings, an ally of Peters testified about election fraud, highlighting the prominence of these claims in her case. The guilty verdict marks a significant development for Peters, who was once hailed as a hero by election deniers. Despite defense attempts at an acquittal, the judge denied the motion. The trial has featured closing arguments and jury deliberations, with the outcome raising questions about the consequences for individuals who promote unfounded election fraud allegations.

name: Bad Monkey
summary: Apple TV+'s "Bad Monkey" receives mixed reviews. Some critics praise its strong cast and intriguing story, while others find it disjointed and lacking focus. The show's setting in Florida is highlighted as both a cinematic asset and a source of weather-related challenges during filming. The episodic reviews of the first two episodes mention a motormouthed Vince Vaughn carrying the comedy and a plot that abruptly thrusts the protagonist into a chaotic situation. The release schedule indicates a weekly episode release pattern, and the overall assessment of Season 1 remains to be determined as more episodes air.

name: Colin Kaepernick
summary: There are multiple reports regarding the future of Colin Kaepernick. Jim Harbaugh, the head coach of the Chargers, has expressed interest in bringing Kaepernick onto his coaching staff. Kaepernick is reportedly considering the offer. Despite not playing in the NFL for the past seven years, Kaepernick has been training and believes he could still contribute to a team's success. Additionally, Kaepernick has expressed an interest in playing flag football for Team USA at the 2028 Olympics.

name: COVID-19
summary: In the midst of the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic, various sources provide updates and information on the virus's global impact, epidemiological situation, and the latest developments in vaccines, variants, and masking recommendations. A California grant program focuses on supporting adult day services during the COVID-19 crisis, while UCHealth Today provides regular updates on the virus. UC San Francisco offers expert guidance on the proper use of face masks to minimize transmission risks. Mesa County Public Health announces limited availability of COVID-19 vaccines while awaiting updated versions. Amidst the challenges, the story of Noah Lyles' resilience shines through as he earns a bronze medal in the 200-meter dash despite a COVID-19 diagnosis. Science Magazine highlights the need to address disparities in COVID-19 vaccine coverage and outcomes, while Health Essentials explores the effectiveness of Lysol Disinfecting Wipes against the virus.

name: 2025 Social Security COLA increase
summary: Several news outlets have reported on the estimated cost-of-living adjustment (COLA) for Social Security benefits in 2025, citing a projection of 2.6%. This adjustment is intended to offset inflation, but the estimate has been downgraded from earlier projections due to a modest slowdown in inflation. Despite the lower COLA, increased daily expenses continue to impact seniors significantly. However, there is some uncertainty as to whether the 2.6% adjustment will be the final figure, as it is still a preliminary estimate.
